Subject:
B.Tech (Honours) programme (relevant only to 5th semster B.Tech /DD
 students)

Body:
b'     Dear Students    Greetings.  From 2010, the B.Tech (Honours) programme is in operation .    Enrollment into B.Tech (Honours) programme for the year 2016 .    B.Tech and Dual Degree students of 2014 batch having a CGPA &n;bsp;  of  8.5 and who have cleared all the courses in the first attempt can opt  for B.Tech (Honours) in this (July Nov 2016) semester.   Rules:   (i) Those who opt for B.Tech (Honours) must register for 12 additional PMT  credits.      (ii) Students can register for a maximum of 2 additional PMT courses in a  semester from the Honours basket of courses over and above the courses  prescribed in the B.Tech curriculum from 5th semester onwards.    (iii) Departmentwise list of courses as proposed by the departments as Honours level courses and approved  by the senate is available in the department .    (iv) Project work is a must for B.Tech (Honours) students in B.Tech programme.  Those who have registered for B.Tech (Honours) must maintain an average CGPA   of 8.5. Otherwise, they will be awarded only B.Tech Degree.    (v) Extra credits earned by the students will be counted for prizes and awards.     To enroll, please write an application to Dean Academic courses and forward the same with the approval of Faculty adviser and HoD.       Dean Academic Courses IIT Madras, Chennai 600036, India.  The information in the mail is meant only for the earmarked recipients and should not be shared or made public without permission     '

